para_trans: Search-cum Selection Committee for the selection of Technical Member (State) of the State Benches of GST Appellate Tribunal -reg.
1) Notification No S.O. 4073 (E) dated 14/9/2023 issued by Department of

As per Ref (1) above, three State Benches of the Goods and Service Tax Appellate Tribunal (GSTAT) have been constituted for the State of Maharashtra and Goaas per section 109 (4) of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (CGST Act).

The Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017, Section 110 (4) (a) provides for constitution of a Search-cum-Selection Committeefor the recommendations in respect of selection of Technical Member (State) of the State Bench of the GSTAT.

As per the provisions of Section 110 (4) (a) of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 and nominations received from the Hon'ble High Court of Judicature at Bombay and the Chief Secretariat, the Search-cum-Selection Committee constituted for making recommendations for the appointment of Technical Member (State) of the State Benches of the GSTAT shall be consistent of: -

a) Hon'ble Chief Justice of the High Court, Bombay (Chairperson) b) Hon'ble Justice (Retd) Shri Sunil B. Shukre (Member) c) Chief Secretary, Government of Maharashtra (Member) d) Additional Chief Secretary, General Administrative Department-Services, Government of Maharashtra (Member) e) Additional Chief Secretary / Principal Secretary / Secretary, Financial Reforms, Government of Maharashtra (Member Secretary)
4. Secretarial assistance to the Committee shall be provided by Finance Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai.
